<FIRST>u a AM-MissTeenUSA     07-26 0236</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Miss Teen USA,0243</SECOND>
<HEAD>Miss Idaho Chosen as Miss Teen USA</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN BERNARDINO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tearful Miss Idaho was crowned
Miss Teen USA 1989 on Tuesday in a pageant televised in two dozen
countries.
   Brandi Sherwood, 18, of Idaho Falls, was chosen from among 51
contestants, representing each state and the District of Columbia.
   The seventh annual show was held at the National Orange
Showgrounds in this city 50 miles east of downtown Los Angeles.
   She received a crown and a bouquet of flowers on stage from her
predecessor, Mindy Duncan, 17, of Newberg, Ore., pageant officials
said.
   Ms. Sherwood wins nearly $150,000 in cash and prizes, including
a car, jewelry, one-year scholarship and three-week European
``fashion study tour.'' Various sponsors supplied the prizes.
   The runner-up was Miss Teen Kentucky, Kristi Dawn Hicks, 17, of
Bardstown, Ken.
   Second runnerup was Miss Teen Vermont, Kara Quinn, 15, of
Rutland, Vt. Third runnerup was Miss Teen Texas, Kristi Wright, 16,
Del Rio, Texas, and fourth runnerup was Miss Teen North Dakota,
Heidi Jo Lanseth, 17, of Fargo, N.D.
   The show, which aired on CBS, was hosted by talk show host Wil
Shriner and Marcia Strassman, who appeared in the movie ``Honey, I
Shrunk the Kids.''
   The contestants, ages 15 to 18, were judged on the basis of two
days of interviews, an evening gown competition and a swimsuit
contest, said Mary Chervenak, a pageant spokeswoman.
</TEXT>
