<HEAD>Fitzwater: Bloch On The Brain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   White House officials aren't saying much about
Felix Bloch, the State Department diplomat being investigated as a
possible spy, but that doesn't mean they aren't thinking about him.
   Press secretary Marlin Fitzwater, fielding a question Tuesday
about another matter, said President Bush has repeatedly
``expressed his outrage'' about influence-peddling at the
Department of Housing and Urban Development and ``talked to
