<SECOND>PM-Daily News Publisher,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>LA Daily News Names New Publisher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cable marketing executive David J. Auger will
become publisher of the Los Angeles Daily News next month, owner
Jack Kent Cooke announced.
   Auger, 33, has been vice president@marketing for Cooke
CableVision Inc., also owned by Cooke, for the past year. He was
formerly a marketing executive with the cable division of Warner
Communications Inc.
   ``David Auger has proven himself as one of the best marketing
executives in the communications business,'' Cooke said Tuesday.
   Auger, who assumes his new job Aug. 7, said in a statement he
has ``high expectations for the future of one of America's
fastest-growing newspapers.''
   For the six-month period ending March 31, the Daily News
reported weekday circulation of 183,402, up from 174,599 in the
corresponding period a year earlier, and Sunday circulation of
201,533, up from 193,076.
   The figures were supplied by the Audit Bureau of Circulations of
Schaumburg, Ill., a newspaper industry auditing and monitoring
concern.
   Auger succeeds R. Steve Morris, who resigned last month to
pursue other business interests.
