<FIRST>r i PM-Nicaragua     07-26 0138</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Nicaragua,0143</SECOND>
<HEAD>Violeta Chamorro Would Accept Presidential Nomination</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Violeta Barrios de Chamorro, editor of
the opposition newspaper La Prensa, says she will accept the
presidential nomination if she is chosen by a coalition of
opposition parties.
   The National Opposition Union, or UNO, a coalition of 14
opposition parties spanning the ideologial spectrum, was to meet
tonight to decide on a single opposition candidate.
   ``If UNO decides that I am the best candidate to win the battle
for democracy, I could not say no,'' Mrs. Chamorro said Tuesday
night.
   The opposition alliance, whose members include conservatives,
moderates and communists, will choose a candidate to challenge the
Sandinistas in the February 1990 presidential elections.
   Since coming to power in 1979, the Sandinistas have frequently
censored and closed the La Prensa daily and other opposition media.
</TEXT>
