<HEAD>Suspects Nabbed After Asking Police To Send A Cab</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIBERTY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men have been arrested after they
mistakenly called police instead of the cab company they needed for
their getaway after allegedly comitting a burglary.
   ``We don't know how or why they called the Liberty Police
Department unless they knew they were being chased by police and
dialed it subconsciously,'' said Chief Edward Eisely.
   He said police received a report Tuesday that someone had been
robbed of $40 by two men.
   Shortly after the dispatcher alerted local taxi companies, a man
called, saying he needed a cab right away for a ride to Loch
Sheldrake, a village 3 miles away.
