stopped a taxi that picked the suspects up, Eisely said.
   The two men were charged with second-degree burglary.
   ``The only other time I can think of something like this
happening was a few years ago in New York City when these guys
tried to rob a bank during FBI payday,'' Eisely said. ``They asked
the teller for money, and they heard about 15 guns clicking behind
them.''
