westbound lanes. Police cleared the freeway ahead of the horses to
Interstate 25, where the horses headed north in the southbound
lanes.
   Police managed to direct them onto a service road, and they
finally were herded onto a street.
   One horse fell, giving pursuers a chance to collar him. The
other two continued west until they saw other horses grazing in a
field and joined them.
   The animals' owner was cited with three counts of animals
running at large.
