<HEAD>Suspect in Murder of Singer's Daughter Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The shooting death of the suspect in the slaying
of the daughter of late soul singer Jackie Wilson means the case
will go unresolved.
   Gary Johnson, 28, was shot several times early Sunday as he
entered a Detroit home, police said.
   Johnson was charged with second-degree murder in the death of
Jacqueline Wilson 37, last year. Police believe she was hit by
gunfire Johnson intended for another man.
   Johnson, who faced an Oct. 2 trial, had been free on $50,000
bond.
   Detroit detectives declined to discuss a possible motive, but
said the shooting was unrelated to Wilson's death.
