<FIRST>r i AM-China-Floods     07-26 0231</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-China-Floods,0237</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rains, Flooding Kill 197 in China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A week of heavy rains and flooding has left 197
people dead in Zhejiang and Hebie provinces, and 21 people are
missing, official reports said Wednesday.
   More than 1,700 people have died in flooding this summer across
China.
   In the coastal province of Zhejiang, which was hit by Typhoon
Hope last week, 122 people died, 901 people were injured and 21
people were missing, the Xinhua News Agency said. It said the
province had suffered losses of $286 million.
   The storms that hit central and southern Hebei last week killed
75 people, injured 1,184, and destroyed 240,000 homes, the People's
Daily said. The rain flooded 7 million acres of farmland, washed
away 220,000 tons of grain, and cut off power, telecommunications
and transport, the newspaper reported.
   In central Hebei's Baoding prefecture, about 95 miles south of
Beijing, 220,000 people were stranded after about 22{ inches of
rain fell. In the city of Cangzhou, nine inches of rain fell in
three hours.
   While parts of China are suffering from too much rain, a severe
drought has hit western China's Xinjiang province and parts of
central Liaoning province, in the northeast. Xinhua said rain in
Xinjiang is down by 25 percent to 46 percent.
   Locusts destroyed 5 million acres of crops and rats damaged 3.2
million acres, the news agency said.
</TEXT>
