<DATELINE>GALLOWAY TOWNSHIP, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus filled with gamblers bound
for Atlantic City's casinos overturned this morning, injuring at
least 10 people seriously, police and hospital officials said.
   The Saddle River Tours bus overturned shortly before 11:30 a.m.,
blocking both southbound lanes of the Garden State Parkway, Trooper
John Zulawski said. He said troopers at the scene counted 37 people
aboard.
   But paramedics said 47 to 50 people were taken from the bus to
five hospitals with injuries ranging from cuts and bruises to
broken ribs.
   Sherry Spatz, a spokeswoman for Atlantic City Medical Center's
mainland division, said 10 people suffered serious injuries, but
she could not provide details.
   The passengers were mostly elderly people who had boarded the
bus at Rutherford in northern New Jersey and were bound for Caesars
Atlantic City casino hotel, police and hospital officials said.
   There was no immediate explanation of what caused the bus to
turn on its side.
   A woman who answered the telephone at the Lodi-based bus company
would not talk about the incident. She hung up before giving her
name.
   Zulawski said traffic was being diverted off the parkway at the
Smithville exit, just north of the Atlantic City exit.
