<HEAD>62 Children Become Ill After Lunch at Youth Center</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sixty-two children were rushed to hospitals
Wednesday, complaining of stomach cramps and nausea after eating
lunch at a youth center, officials said. Some were driven on
commandeered city buses.
   Hospital officials at Orlando Regional Medical Center, Humana
Hospital and AMI Medical Center reported no life-threatening
problems.
   The children reportedly ate a lunch of ham and cheese sandwiches
and pears provided by a food service company contracted by city
