transit buses commandeered by rescue personnel called to the
Frontline Outreach youth center.
   Seventeen children were taken to Humana Hospital, and 16 to AMI
by emergency vehicles.
   Most were expected to be released to their parents, officials
said.
   Frontline Outreach sponsors a series of athletic, social,
counseling and education programs for young people.
