<SECOND>AM-Revenge Shooting,0289</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Angered Over Dismissal of Rape Case Shoots Man She Accused</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman enraged by the district attorney's
refusal to prosecute a rape case shot her alleged attacker eight
times, then bludgeoned him with a beer bottle, police said
Wednesday.
   The man was in critical condition at Cedars-Sinai Medical
Center, a hospital spokeswoman said.
   Elizabeth Gooden, 26, and her brother, Leroy Gooden, 31, were
booked for investigation of attempted murder and held without bail,
detectives said. Police allege the brother ran off with the gun
used in the attack.
   Miss Gooden called police Friday and alleged that she had been
raped by Wilson Picquet, 38, after a night of drinking in his
apartment, Detective John Bunch said. Picquet was booked for
investigation of rape.
   Miss Gooden, Picquet, detectives and a deputy district attorney
met Tuesday to examine the case. Picquet said Miss Gooden had
agreed to have sex with him, but that the couple then argued.
   The deputy district attorney dismissed the case, saying it
hinged on Miss Gooden's word against Picquet's.
   Bunch said the woman gave no indication that she was upset
enough to take any action against Picquet, who lived in the same
apartment complex.
   Later, when Picquet walked through the gates of the apartment
building, Bunch said, Miss Gooden fired one shot at close range
into his chest.
   She then stood over him and fired seven more shots from a
.380-caliber automatic and finally pitched the beer bottle at him,
the detective said.
   Miss Gooden allegedly handed the gun to her brother, who ran
from the area. He was arrested a few blocks away _ without the gun,
Bunch said.
