<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Gerber     07-26 0116</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Gerber,0121</SECOND>
<HEAD>Baby Food Maker Reports First-Quarter Surge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FREMONT, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Special baby food promotions helped push
Gerber Products Co.'s first-quarter earnings up 45.6 percent, the
company said Tuesday.
   Gerber reported earnings of $26.8 million, or $1.41 a share, for
its first fiscal quarter ending June 30, up from $18.4 million, or
93 cents a share, in the comparable period last year.
   Sales for the quarter totaled $273 million, a 10 percent
increase from $248.2 million a year earlier.
   ``Baby food unit volume increased 10.4 percent, as the timing of
promotions for First Foods fruits and vegetables and for baby week
added sales to the quarter,'' said David Johnson, chairman and
chief executive officer.
</TEXT>
