<HEAD>Close Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New throughout</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks declined Wednesday despite economic news
that was better than expected.
   The government's report that Britain's trade deficit in June was
lower than estimated failed to inspire the market, though analysts
said the figures reduced the likelihood of a further rise in
British interest rates.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed 4.9
points, or 0.2 percent, lower at 2,264.5.
   The Financial Times 30-share index closed off 2.6 points at
1,883.4. The Financial Times 500-share index fell 2.02 points to
close at 1,284.04.
   Volume totaled 315.3 million shares, compared with 461.7 million
shares Tuesday.
