<FILEID>AP-NR-07-26-89 2238EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>a f PM-HomesellingAdvice Adv27   07-26 0233</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Homeselling Advice, Adv 27,0245</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv27</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release PMs Thursday July 27 and Thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-On The Money</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some tips for do-it-yourselfers in the home-selling
market, according to J.R. Paine, author of ``The 30 Day Way To Sell
Your Home'':
   _Begin by making a checklist of all critical areas of your home,
starting with the front yard, eyeing areas that need repair.
   _Dress up your home. ``A house with a neglected appearance
loudly tells the prospective buyers that its owners do not like it,
do not want it, and do not think it has any value or worth.''
   _Get a reliable appraisal of your home's true value.
   _Select the best time to market your home. ``As a rule warm
weather is more conducive to home sales in cold climates, and cold
weather is more conducive in home sales in warm climates.''
   _Get a ``For Sale'' sign.
   _Select a real estate attorney.
   _Select a title company to do your title work.
   _Contact a local lender to obtain current interest rates.
   _Use ``action-inspiring'' advertising expressions, emphasizing
money appeal with words like ``economical,'' ``bargain'' or
``value''; or ego appeal, with words like ``elegant,'' ``graceful''
or ``fashionable.'' A homeowner might describe negative attributes
like a dirt road, as a low traffic street safe for children and
pets, or run-down property as a handyman's dream.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv PMs Thursday July 27</NOTE>
