<HEAD>Du Pont Second-Quarter Earnings Up 12 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Du Pont Co. on Wednesday reported
second- quarter earnings of $714 million, a 12 percent increase
from $639 million in the same period last year.
   Earnings per share were $3.02, compared with $2.67 in the second
quarter of 1988.
   Du Pont Chairman Edgar S Woolard J.r said the increase reflected
``continued strength in worldwide demand in a broad range of the
company's businesses, with particularly good results for industrial
products and petroleum.''
   The chemical company's quarterly sales were $9.3 billion, up 11
percent from $8.3 billion for the same 1988 quarter.
   Net income for the first six months of 1989 was up 18 percent to
$1.45 billion from $1.2 billion for the first half of 1988.
   Sales for the first half were $18 billion, an 11 percent
increase over $16.2 billion in the same period last year.
