<HEAD>Yields Fall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on two-year Treasury notes fell in
Wednesday's auction to the lowest level in 15 months.
   The average yield was 7.75 percent, down from 8.26 percent at
the last auction on June 27.
   It was the lowest rate since two-year notes averaged 7.64
percent on April 27, 1988. The notes will carry a coupon interest
rate of 7} percent.
   A total of $9.0 billion in notes was sold out of bids totaling
$28.7 billion.
